OL,3,CWording of proposed assisted dying law
OL,4,Con Isle of Man debated
OL,6,FThe clauses stage of the Bill will
OL,7,Fcontinue on June 25, with the Third
OL,8,FReading possibly now not taking place
OL,9,Funtil after summer.
OL,11,FCampaigners have previously said if
OL,12,Fthe Bill gains royal assent next year,
OL,13,Fassisted dying could be available to
OL,14,Feligible Manx residents from 2027.
OL,16,FBut Chief Minister Alfred Cannan has
OL,17,Fproposed that the overall Bill should
OL,18,Fhave to be put to a referendum before
OL,19,Fbecoming law.
